The move came after engagement between the Central Organisation of Trade Unions Secretary General Francis Atwoli and Qatar's Labour Minister, Ali bins Samikh Al Marri in Doha. Recruitment offices that have been shut down include those in Starch, Anand, Sunrise, Dubai, Frame, among others. They are accused of violating law by sneaking Kenyans into the Middle East. This is part of monitoring efforts to preserve the rights of employers of domestic workers and improvement of working conditions, as well as the welfare of Kenyas working in Qatar. --The East African--